Add a `src/scheduler.js` module that implements a simple task scheduler. It should export `schedule(name, intervalMs, fn)` to register a named recurring task (using setInterval), `cancel(name)` to stop a named task, and `list()` to return an array of currently active task names. Add `tests/scheduler.test.js` that verifies: scheduling a task causes fn to be called after the interval, cancelling stops future calls, and list() reflects active tasks. Use setTimeout/setInterval (no external libraries).